================================================================================
ABOUT THIS ADD-ON
================================================================================

This add-on is an independent implementation for ingesting Akamai WAF/SIEM
security events into Splunk, built on the Splunk Universal Configuration
Console (UCC) framework v6.3.0.

This add-on is NOT affiliated with, endorsed by, or a derivative work of
the official "Akamai SIEM Integration" (Splunkbase App #4310) published by
Akamai Technologies, Inc. The core data collection logic was written from
scratch by Ensign InfoSecurity Indonesia.

The development of this add-on was inspired by and references the
functionality provided by the official Akamai SIEM Integration, with
significant enhancements including:
  - Splunk UCC framework migration (multi-account, multi-proxy, encrypted
    credential storage, SSL verification, custom sourcetype)
  - Offset-based checkpointing
  - Per-config-ID input separation
  - Splunk 9.4.x and 10.x cross-compatibility

